    "title": "Oblivion",
    "year": 2020,
    "category": "3D, VR and sculpture",
    "material": "VR headset, metal structure",
    "description": "Oblivion is a large metallic installation where the visitor can enter a virtual landscape of the scannet Nikehallen in Konstakademien. Each visitor can experience the space in their own way, as the virtual space is generated differently by the movement of the visitors. The installation explores the relationship between physical and virtual space, and how our perception of space can be altered and transformed through technology.",
