    "category": "Sculpture",
    "material": "Acrystal, walnut frame",
    "size": "98 x 88 cm",
    "description": "“Meänmaa” – our land – is a work that revolves around imprints, belonging and the emotional charge of a place. It carries a longing to take a place with you, to hold on to something that otherwise slips away. In Meänmaa, the place becomes both present and absent – ​​something to touch, but also something inanimate and only a hint. An attempt to own a place through memory, when language, culture or history have been silenced.",
